Class Vector_Network2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.leeds.ccg.andyt.vector.geometry.Vector_AbstractGeometry2D
      • uk.ac.leeds.ccg.andyt.vector.geometry.Vector_Network2D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Vector_Network2D
extends Vector_AbstractGeometry2D
implements Serializable
    Class for networks. These comprise a HashMap of Vector_Point2D instances each linked to a HashSet of Connections. Each Connection comprises of a Vector_Point2D instance and a value.

      • addToNetwork

        public void addToNetwork(Vector_Network2D a_Network,
                         int operator)
        Adds the points and connections from a_Network into this. If lowest is true then for connections between the same start and end points of the same type, the lowest value of these is maintained, otherwise the highest is.
        Parameters:
        a_Network - Vector_Network2D
        operator - If operator == 1, then min; operator == 2, then max; operator == 3, then increment; operator == 4, then sum.
